This may be the Knox Presbyterian Church. A <a href="http://www.archives.presbyterian.org.nz/WaikatoPresbytery.htm" rel="nofollow">note on the NZ Presbyterian Church website</a> says that &quot;The wooden Church, which had been built in 1910, was blown off its piles in 1930. Butresses were then added to the exterior of the building which cost the Parish £68 pounds &amp; ten shillings.&quot;

Does anyone know if the building still exists, and what its street address is/was? I'd love to add it to our map.

-- Courtney
